article.headline: Liberty 70, Radford 62
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. (AP) -- David Dees scored 23 as Liberty came back in the second half to beat Radford 70-62 Saturday. Larry Blair had 18 points for Liberty (12-13, 10-5 Big South Conference), Brian Woodson had 13 and Leo Lightbourne added 11 and nine rebounds. Radford (10-15, 5-9) led 32-24 at the break. Olumuyiwa Popoola started out the second half with a jumper, but a 7-2 Liberty run cut that lead to five with 16:38 remaining. An 11-2 run later in the game put Liberty ahead 54-50 with 8:19 to go and Liberty never trailed again. The Flames shot 53.1 percent in the second half while holding Radford to only 35.7 percent. Liberty outrebounded Radford 44-32. Andre Bynum led Radford with 14 points, while Brandon Jeffers and Popoola had 13 apiece. Chris Oliver came off the bench to score 12.
